^^"看到經驗是用刷的 刷~~五十萬經驗進賬 越練越上癮
終於在 努力下得到肥吱吱翅膀0.0這是我玩天傳以來的夢想 終於實現了
-0-這裡沒外掛 大家都可以玩的很愉快哦 但也要適應 菲律賓人的白木-0-  
主神我有去打過 大概9X去打 沒出現被一昭秒的情形 因為那邊主神沒人用"超人"工具
有點像是台版一開始的主神@@" 而大家這麼守規矩的原因 
因為菲律賓的防外掛算是最好的 比日本還好 他們最近研發一種新的程式 用什麼東西都破解不了 另外也是一個人被鎖整盟就鎖@@"警惕作用很大 
--------------------------------------------------------------------
以下是菲律賓天傳常用的詞語 轉貼自大陸網站
For starter, lets begin w/ the common words that are use for chatting to all Philippines online game. Some are also standards in other online programs. 

Note:?tagalog? is the native language of the Philippines. 

newbie / noob ? slang word for beginners, new player in the game. Usage: "I'm a newbie!". 

import ? means foreigner in the game. Usage: "I'm an import" or "She's imported". 

IMO ? abbreviation for ?in my opinion?. 

FYI ? abbreviation for ?for your information?. 

BTW ? abbreviation for ?by the way?. 

IRL ? abbreviation for ?in real life?. 

LOL ? laughing out loud 

lolz ? some ?under achievement? Pilipinos always mistaken LOL as an abbreviated tagalog word for crazy which is ?u l o l?. They though that when you say LOL, you are referring to them as crazy. Those ?educated? one are trying hard to correct this one so they came up of the word ?lolz? (a decorative way of saying LOL). With the letter ?z? at the end, it now separates the LOL from ?u l o l? and their meaning. 

ASL (age / s e x / location) ? Abbreviated words. "S e x" can be distinguished by simply putting letter ?m? for male and ?f? for female. 

NP ? abbreviation for "no problem". 

TC ? abbreviation for "take care". 

TY ? abbreviation for "thank you". 

BB ? abbreviation for "bye bye" or simple bye, goodbye. 

"p u t a" ? spanish origin (adopted in the Philippines) word for "b i t c h", whore, slut or prostitute. May came in many form like pota, pucha.. since this word is filtered in-game. 

pok-pok ? almost same as "p u t a". Pok-pok means a girl who like to have "s e x" for free while "p u t a" offer herself in exchange for money. 

putang ina mo ? slang for ?'p u t a' ang ina mo?; a phrase in tagalog meaning ?your mother is a 'b i t c h'?. 

asa ? commonly use slang word by many ?misbehaving players?. A tagalog word for hope. Usage: ?asa ka?, meaning ?you?re hoping? or in in-game use: ?keep hoping?. 

bobo ? an offensive word in tagalog meaning; dumb, un-literate, dim bulb, lack of knowledge. Usage: ?bobo ka", meaning ?you're dumb?. 

tae ? tagalog word for "s h i t", poop, stool, feces. Usage: you probably get the idea already when somebody say ?tae ka?. 

sawsaw ? "Sawsaw" is when you hit a target that somebody is already attacking. By doing so, you will share some of the experience from that target w/ that somebody. Players don?t like ?sawsaw? because their not getting all the experience that they deserve from killing the target (monster). 

The word sawsaw is an active verb or action word in tagalog meaning, ?the act of dipping a food into a sauce?. It?s just like you?re dipping into somebody else sauce when you do this in on-line game. Try to avoid this act for it may result in an argument. 

chixilog / chicklog / chicksilog - slang or shortcut for "chicks na may itlog (chicks w/ balls)". A term used for a female character in the game having a guy player. 

S> ?text? ? it mean ?selling? something. 

B> ?text? ? it mean ?buying? something. 

T> ?text? ? it mean ?trading? something. 

R> ?text? ? it mean ?recruiting? someone. 

AFK ? away from keyboard 

DC ? disconnect 

OL ? online 

PM ? private message 

gm ? guild master 

GM ? game master 

SR ? success rate 

PK ? player kill 

PVP ? player vs player 

PVM ? player vs monster 

P2P ? pay to play 

PHP ? Philippine Peso, the currency in the Philippines. 

resu ? resurrect 

pot ? usable item that restore your HP and / or TP / MP (mana).
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
hima - short for Nagamudra Hima 
kubs, monks - another term for Kubasang 
jols - refers to "jewel", stone used for resurrection 
BH - abbreviation for the ashram BROTHERHOOD 
BH, pepsi blue, "pajama" - "blue heart" which refers to Jama skill of D/G 
A/R - Asura / Rakshasa 
N/K - Naga / Kimnara 
D/G - Deva / Garuda 
Y/G - Yaksa / Gandharva 
siopao - refers to the Trata skill of D/G 
eye - refers to "third-eye", Rocana skill of D/G and A/R 
wafu - slang for "gwapo" or goodlooking 
fafi - slang for "papa" 
amp - slang for "amputa" (read as: ang /\/\/\) - b**** 
wakoko, wakeke, ahihi or the like - same as lolz 
buff - refers to support skills of Y/G 
wing - refers to the "speed" skill of Y/G 
QS - short for the item Quality Sjifrian (100% self resurrection item) 
AS - attack success 
AS - amanda's secret, item to change physical appearance 
PL - party leader 
GM - game master or guild master 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
A few items via Game language.  
RCOS - Roha Chabi of Spells - Rare TP Recovery Belt 
RCOL - Roha Chabi of Life - Rare HP Recovery Belt 
TOPW - Talwar of Primitive Warrior - Rare One hand sword 
TOW - Talwar of Warrior - Better Rare One Hand Sword 
SOM - Suraka of Muscle - Rare Shortblade/Dagger 
SOWB - Suraka of WildBeast - Better Rare Shortblad/Dagger 
Stones - Any regular upgrade Jewel (dipa, illa, azis, surapa, prajati) 

A few Area/Locations via Game language. 
ToF - Temple of Fire (Hunting Bongbos, Flowers) 
Hill - Reference to safe spot in ToF (Hunting Bongbos, Flowers) 
Monks - Residential Area - Pamir (Hunting Kubasang) 
Decos - North/East Gate Exile (Hunting Ban Dopang for Decohorns) 
ET - Emperors Tomb (Hunting for 68-74 items) 

Few in-game phrases/abbreviations/translations via Game Language. 
TUF - Top Up First - Regarding to load trading 
OMW - On My Way... 
d2 = Here 
PL = Party Leader 
ako/ko = Me, Mine 
Ikaw/kita/ka = You, Your 
cno? = sino - who/whom? 
ano? = what? 
p0?ta (or anything sounding similar) = bad word = b*tch 
Sali - Join/Include/add 
Lvl mo? = Your level? 
Gap = Level Gap, 20 level difference = Prana Monster 
Pwede ex. pwede sali ako = Can you add me? 
Po = please/expression of respect to elder/more experienced ppl. 
Pahingi Items Po = Give me Items Please... (Popular exp. in first 3 maps) 
toinkz = Sound game makes when character dies 


 


